## Standard Production VPC Layout

```
VPC: 10.0.0.0/16
│
├── ap-south-1a
│   ├── Public Subnet:  10.0.1.0/24  → Route: 0.0.0.0/0 → IGW
│   └── Private Subnet: 10.0.3.0/24  → Route: 0.0.0.0/0 → NAT GW (AZ-a)
│
└── ap-south-1b
    ├── Public Subnet:  10.0.2.0/24  → Route: 0.0.0.0/0 → IGW
    └── Private Subnet: 10.0.4.0/24  → Route: 0.0.0.0/0 → NAT GW (AZ-b)

Public subnets:  ALB, NAT Gateways, Bastion hosts (if any)
Private subnets: EC2 app servers, RDS, ElastiCache, EKS nodes
```

This is the layout you will use for almost every production system.

