## CIDR Planning

Plan your CIDR blocks before you build. Overlapping CIDRs break VPC peering and on-premises connectivity.

```
/16 → 65,534 IPs  (use for VPC)
/24 → 254 IPs     (use for subnets)
/28 → 14 IPs      (minimum subnet size, good for VPC endpoints, load balancers)

AWS reserves 5 IPs per subnet:
  x.x.x.0   → network address
  x.x.x.1   → VPC router
  x.x.x.2   → DNS
  x.x.x.3   → future use
  x.x.x.255 → broadcast
So a /24 gives you 251 usable IPs.
```

