## VPC Endpoints

VPC Endpoints let services in private subnets talk to AWS services (S3, DynamoDB, SSM, ECR) without going through the NAT Gateway. Saves NAT Gateway data costs and keeps traffic on the AWS network.

```bash
# S3 Gateway Endpoint (free)
aws ec2 create-vpc-endpoint \
  --vpc-id $VPC_ID \
  --service-name com.amazonaws.ap-south-1.s3 \
  --vpc-endpoint-type Gateway \
  --route-table-ids $PRIV_RT

# SSM Interface Endpoint (needed for SSM Session Manager in private subnets)
aws ec2 create-vpc-endpoint \
  --vpc-id $VPC_ID \
  --service-name com.amazonaws.ap-south-1.ssm \
  --vpc-endpoint-type Interface \
  --subnet-ids $PRIV_SUBNET_A $PRIV_SUBNET_B \
  --security-group-ids $SG_ID
```

