## Debugging Connectivity

```bash
# From inside a private instance — can I reach the internet?
curl https://google.com

# Can I reach another instance by private IP?
nc -zv 10.0.3.15 8080

# Check route table associations
aws ec2 describe-route-tables \
  --filters "Name=vpc-id,Values=$VPC_ID" \
  --query 'RouteTables[*].[RouteTableId,Associations[*].SubnetId,Routes[*].[DestinationCidrBlock,GatewayId,NatGatewayId]]' \
  --output table

# VPC Flow Logs — log all traffic in/out of your VPC
aws ec2 create-flow-logs \
  --resource-type VPC \
  --resource-ids $VPC_ID \
  --traffic-type ALL \
  --log-destination-type cloud-watch-logs \
  --log-group-name /aws/vpc/flowlogs \
  --deliver-logs-permission-arn arn:aws:iam::ACCOUNT_ID:role/flowlogs-role
```

