## Key Insight for DevOps

The most common VPC mistake is putting everything in public subnets because it's easier. Do not do this in production. Your databases, app servers, and EKS nodes belong in private subnets. Only load balancers and NAT gateways go in public subnets.

The second most common mistake is forgetting that NAT Gateway costs money. A pair of NAT Gateways (one per AZ for HA) costs around $65/month minimum, plus data transfer. For dev/test, a single NAT Gateway is fine.